  <metadata>
    <id>MyCouch</id>
    <version>0.17.0</version>
    <title>MyCouch - CouchDb and Cloudant client</title>
    <authors>danielwertheim</authors>
    <owners>danielwertheim</owners>
    <licenseUrl>https://github.com/danielwertheim/MyCouch#license</licenseUrl>
    <projectUrl>https://github.com/danielwertheim/MyCouch</projectUrl>
    <iconUrl>http://www.mycouchclient.com/logos/mycouch-nuget.png</iconUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>MyCouch is the simple asynchronous CouchDb and Cloudant client for .Net - builds on top of the asynchronous HTTP client and uses JSON.Net to provide flexible serialization behaviour. It tries to keep the domain language of CouchDb instead of bringing in generic repositories and other confusing stuff. MyCouch lets you work with raw JSON and/or entities/POCOS without requiring any implementation of interfaces, baseclasses etc. MyCouch provides you with some model conventions like injection of $doctype to the document. It is plug-gable. If you don't like some piece, then hook in your implementation instead.

      If you want Cloudant specific features like Lucene Searches, go with the "MyCouch.Cloudant" package instead.

      Supports .Net4.0, .Net4.5 and Windows store apps (WinRT).

      Please NOTE. This is not an official Cloudant package.

      Please NOTE. If you don't have NuGet up to date, some uses has had issues with resolving dependencies.</description>
    <summary>Simple async CouchDb and Cloudant client.</summary>
    <releaseNotes>Can be found on project site: https://github.com/danielwertheim/mycouch/wiki/release-notes</releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright 2013 Daniel Wertheim</copyright>
    <language />
    <tags>couchdb cloudant nosql json document-db documents poco async asynchronous winrt</tags>
